{
  "text": "The It\u00f4 integrals with respect to G-L\u00e9vy processes. In the subsection, we introduce the It\u00f4 integrals with respect to G-L\u00e9vy processes under the framework of the above subsection. Let X denote the canonical process on the space, i.e. X t (\u03c9) = \u03c9 t , t \u2208 [0, T ]. So, X is a d-dimensional G-L\u00e9vy process. Although the It\u00f4 integrals with respect to G-Brownian motions have been introduced in [CITATION_1] , we need to introduce two related spaces used in the sequel. Take Next, we introduce the It\u00f4 integrals with respect to random measures. First, define a random measure: for any 0 t T and A \u2208 B(R d \\ {0}),",
